sentence: But our education proceeded at the hands of those others , who were merely competent and conscientious .
mut.sentence: But our education is proceeding at the hands of those others, who are merely competent and conscientious.
reason: 原句中使用的是过去式'proceeded'，表示教育是在过去某个时间点由其他人进行的，已经完成；而变异句中使用的是现在进行时'is proceeding'，表示教育目前仍在由其他人进行中，尚未完成。两个句子的目标词在时态上存在差异，因此具体含义有所不同。

sentence: One survey says that of the 100,000 trained bellringers in England today , only 40,000 of them still ring .
mut.sentence: One survey said that of the 100,000 trained bellringers in England at that time, only 40,000 of them still rang.
reason: 原句中使用的一般现在时'says'表明调查结果在当前仍然有效或相关，而变异句中使用的一般过去时'said'则表明调查结果是过去某个时间点的发现，不一定反映当前情况。

sentence: The 10 deals the Iraqi Oil Ministry reached with foreign oil companies suggest that China , Russia and European oil firms are poised to play a major role in refurbishing Iraq 's oil industry , crippled by decades of war and sanctions .
mut.sentence: The 10 deals the Iraqi Oil Ministry is reaching with foreign oil companies suggest that China, Russia, and European oil firms are expected to play a major role in refurbishing Iraq's oil industry, which has been crippled by decades of war and sanctions.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'deals'在句子中的含义没有明显不同。在原句和变异句中，'deals'都指的是伊拉克石油部与外国石油公司之间已经达成的10项协议。两个句子的主要区别在于时态（原句使用过去时，变异句使用现在进行时），但这并不改变'deals'本身的含义。

sentence: I just felt another aftershock a few seconds ago .
mut.sentence: I am feeling another aftershock right now.
reason: 原句中的'felt'是过去式，表示感觉到震动的动作已经发生并且结束；而变异句中的'feeling'是现在进行时，表示感觉到震动的动作正在发生。因此，两个句子中的目标词'felt'和'feeling'在时态上表示的动作发生的时间点不同。

sentence: Biggest trouble was scared family who could n't get a phone line through , and spent a really horrible hour not knowing .
mut.sentence: The biggest trouble is the scared family who can't get a phone line through, and is spending a really horrible hour not knowing.
reason: 原句中的get是过去式，表示过去某个时间点发生的动作，而变异句中的get是现在进行时，表示正在进行的动作或状态。因此，两个句子的get在时态上表示的动作或状态存在差异。

sentence: For example , first-term members of the House , once the most vulnerable of incumbents , have become virtually immune to defeat .
mut.sentence: For example, first-term members of the House, being the most vulnerable of incumbents, become virtually immune to defeat.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'immune'的含义没有改变。'Immune to defeat'在原句和变异句中的意思都是指议员几乎不可能被击败，即他们对失败有了免疫力。两个句子中使用的是相同的短语和结构来表达这个意思，因此含义相同。

sentence: It gives a lot of flexibility to the process , said John Coequyt , senior Washington representative for the Sierra Club .
mut.sentence: It gives a lot of flexibility to the process, says John Coequyt, senior Washington representative for the Sierra Club.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'Washington' 在句子中的含义没有改变，都指的是John Coequyt作为Sierra Club的高级代表所在的地区或城市，即华盛顿。两个句子中目标词前后的语境完全相同，因此含义一致。

sentence: Actually , he regretted having opened his mouth when the truck came to a stop and the angry driver jumped down from the cab and walked back toward them .
mut.sentence: Actually, he regrets opening his mouth as the truck comes to a stop and the angry driver jumps down from the cab and walks back toward them.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'jumped'和'jumps'在句子中的含义没有本质区别，都描述了司机从驾驶室跳下来的动作。原句使用的是过去式，变异句使用的是现在时，这只是时态的不同，并不影响目标词的含义。

sentence: They will also tell you that even if you hate heights , you can still balloon .
mut.sentence: They also tell you that even if you hate heights, you can still balloon.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'balloon'在句子中的含义没有区别，都是指乘坐热气球的意思。原句中的'that'和变异句中的'they'在语法上虽然有所差异，但这并不影响目标词的含义。

sentence: Nobody witnessed the fall -- just the sickening impact when his body smashed on the pavement just outside the basement delivery entrance .
mut.sentence: Nobody is witnessing the fall -- just the sickening impact as his body smashes on the pavement just outside the basement delivery entrance.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'smashed'和'smashes'在含义上并没有明显的不同。'smashed'是过去式，表明动作已经发生；而'smashes'是现在进行时，表示动作正在发生或者正在被目击。但是，这两个动词都描述了身体撞击地面的动作，其基本含义没有改变，都是指撞击造成的破坏或损伤。因此，从目标词的含义角度来看，它们是相同的。

sentence: If we wish to be serious about American education , we know exactly what to do -- and , just as important , what not to do .
mut.sentence: If we wished to be serious about American education, we knew exactly what to do -- and, just as important, what not to do.
reason: 原句中的wish使用的是现在时态，表示一种一般性的愿望或想法，而变异句中的wished使用的是过去时态，表示在过去某个时间点的愿望或想法。因此，两个句子的目标词wish在时态上有所不同，反映了不同的时间背景和语境含义。

sentence: `` This case , '' they wrote , `` represents the Sheppard v. Maxwell of the 21st century . ''
mut.sentence: This case, they write, represents the Sheppard v. Maxwell of the 21st century.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'case' 在这里都指的是一个具体的案例，即指代'Sheppard v. Maxwell'这个司法案件。两个句子中目标词的含义没有改变，仅仅是动词的时态从过去式'wrote'变为了现在式'write'，但这并不影响目标词'case'的含义。

sentence: It contains the active substance pemetrexed .
mut.sentence: It contained the active substance pemetrexed.
reason: 原句中使用的是现在时态的'contains'，表示目前仍然包含pemetrexed这种活性物质；而变异句中使用的是过去时态的'contained'，表示过去某个时间包含这种活性物质，可能现在不再包含。因此，两个句子中的目标词在时态和意义上有所不同。

sentence: Ruined the damn fishing !
mut.sentence: Ruining the damn fishing!
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'fishing' 在这里都是作为名词使用，表示的是一种活动（钓鱼）。原句使用的是过去式 'ruined' 而变异句使用的是现在进行时 'ruining'，这两个动词形式的不同并不影响目标词 'fishing' 的含义，它们都指代同样的活动。因此，尽管动词形式不同，但目标词 'fishing' 的含义并没有改变。

sentence: Also , the treatment of vomiting should only be together with other supportive measure or other veterinary therapy while addressing the underlying causes of the vomiting .
mut.sentence: Also, the treatment of vomiting was only to be combined with other supportive measures or other veterinary therapies while addressing the underlying causes of vomiting.

sentence: One survey says that of the 100,000 trained bellringers in England today , only 40,000 of them still ring .
mut.sentence: One survey said that of the 100,000 trained bellringers in England at that time, only 40,000 of them still rang.

sentence: The U.N.-sponsored climate conference -- characterized so far by unruly posturing and mutual recriminations -- gained renewed focus Friday with the release of a document outlining ambitious greenhouse-gas reductions over the next 40 years , with industrialized nations shouldering most of the burden in the near term .

reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'posturing'在两个句子中的含义没有区别。在这两个句子中，'posturing'都指的是与会者在气候会议上的姿态和表现，特别是指他们的无序和相互指责的行为，而不是指某种具体的变化或发展。两个句子只是在时态和语态上有所不同，但这并不影响'posturing'这个词的含义。

sentence: Each legislator , after all , is only one out of 535 when it comes to national policy making .

sentence: His shout had been involuntary , something anybody might have done without thinking , on the spur of the moment .

sentence: It often is preceded by the development of polyps in the bowel , which in some cases become increasingly malignant in identifiable stages -- progressing from less severe to deadly -- as though a cascade of genetic damage might be occurring .
mut.sentence: It often was preceded by the development of polyps in the bowel, which in some cases became increasingly malignant in identifiable stages -- progressing from less severe to deadly -- as though a cascade of genetic damage might have been occurring.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'preceded' 在句子中的含义没有区别。两个句子中 'preceded' 均表示某事物在时间或逻辑上前置于另一事物，即肠息肉的发展先于其他情况的发生。两个句子中动词的时态变化（is preceded 和 was preceded）并不影响 'preceded' 这个词本身的含义，而是反映了整个句子时态的变化。
